            <item>
                <title>Multiple Importance Sampling</title>
                <pubDate>Sun, 19 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
                <link>https://64.github.io/multiple-importance-sampling/</link>
                <guid>https://64.github.io/multiple-importance-sampling/</guid>
                <description>&lt;p&gt;In the previous article I described &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;64.github.io&#x2F;monte-carlo&#x2F;&quot;&gt;Importance Sampling&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;, a method for reducing the variance of a Monte Carlo estimator. In this article I will discuss a technique called &lt;em&gt;Multiple Importance Sampling&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; which allows us to combine samples from multiple different probability distributions that we think match the shape of the integrand, reducing variance without introducing bias.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</description>
